pipelineConfig.title: DP4BI_DEV_OHPNM_CDC_SNOWFLAKE_COMPARE
pipelineConfig.description: Compare the number of records between OHPNM tables and Snowflake Tables

configuration.name: preprocessScript
query
configuration.value:
select s.name as TABLE_SCHEMA, t.name as TABLE_NAME, GETDATE() as LAST_UPDATED_DTM 
from sys.tables t join sys.schemas s on t.schema_id = s.schema_id
where t.type = 'U' and 
      (
       (s.name = 'audit' and t.name in('a_credentialing','a_wf_step') )
        or 
	   (s.name = 'dbo' and
         (t.name like 'wf%' or
t.name like 'regi%' or
t.name like 'reg_pr%' or
t.name like 'reg_med%' or
t.name like 'reg_back%' or
t.name like 'reg_specialty%' or
t.name like 'reg_ap%' or
t.name like 'reg_user%' or
t.name like 'user_agent%' or
t.name like 'user_acc%' or
t.name like 'screening%' or
t.name like 'site%' or
t.name like 'application%' or
t.name like 'comm%ev%' or
t.name like 'email' or
t.name like 'credential%' or
t.name like 'reg_owner' or
t.name like 'mail' or
t.name like 'reg_screening' or
t.name like 'provider_risk_level' or
t.name like 'aspnet_users' or
t.name like 'aspnet_roles' or
t.name like 'aspnet_usersinroles' or
t.name like 'user_account_information' or
t.name like 'reg_credentialing' or
t.name like 'provider_type' or
t.name like 'specialty_type' or
t.name like 'county_region' or
t.name like 'county' or
t.name like 'reg_address' or
t.name like 'languages_spoken' or
t.name like 'enroll_status' or
t.name like 'reg_language'
         )
       )  
      )		 
order by 2;
